# Prep detail sections (product spec)

## Order

Frontend **sorts** sections into this order regardless of API order (`SECTION_ORDER` in `app/lib/prepSections.ts`):

1. `summary` — always first when present (card summary + optional detail intro)
2. `research` — “What I found” (narrative, amber-dot bullets, source chips)
3. `pros_cons`
4. `options` — horizontal product cards (snap scroll; single card full width)
5. `comparison` — side-by-side table (scroll if many columns)
6. `draft` — tone pill, bubble, Copy / Send with… / Edit
7. `action_steps`
8. `tips` — stacked cards; warnings tinted
9. `limitations` — honest limits + “what I can do instead”
10. `sources` — standalone pill chips (when emitted as own block)
11. `follow_up` — last; tap → `/dump?prefill=…`

Legacy `search` blocks render like research with title “Here’s the gist.”

## API shapes

Extended `result.blocks` types are parsed in `parsePrepBlocksFromResult` (`app/lib/prepBlocks.ts`). Backend structured output (`prep-result.schema.ts`) still uses the **original** block union; new types appear when the agent/API adds them to JSON. **Normalize + sort** happens in `buildCanonicalSectionsFromPrep`.

## Competitive edge

Dump UX + **this stack** are the primary differentiator: amber system, scannable sections, real product cards, honest limitations, follow-up back into dump.
